lom:description.lom:string: High school experience with programming was the major component of high school computer experience that contributed the most to success in IT in college. Programming courses were especially helpful, as opposed to learning programming on one's own in an undisciplined fashion. Higher grades in programming class were predictive of college success. Knowing applications only without programming was not an indicator of college computer science success. Home computer ownership had a very small positive effect on college CS success.

lom:title.lom:string: An Analysis of Success Factors in College Computer Science: High School Methodology is a Key Element
